WEBVTT

00:01.902 --> 00:02.768
Adult mark:<i> I was hypnotized</i>

00:02.837 --> 00:04.169
<i> By the world</i>
<i> inside our television.</i>

00:04.171 --> 00:07.306
<i> It seemed so far away that</i>
<i>it couldn't possibly be real...</i>

00:07.308 --> 00:08.706
<i> Until it was.</i>

00:08.743 --> 00:10.642
Announcer: [on tv]
from vegas to newfoundland...

00:10.678 --> 00:15.280
The greatest hypnotist on earth!

00:15.282 --> 00:17.883
I am hudaro!

00:18.018 --> 00:19.384
...Two, one...

00:19.386 --> 00:21.320
Aah!
And you'll become...

00:21.455 --> 00:22.988
...A famous opera star!

00:22.990 --> 00:26.959
Now you're napoleon,
and you're a kangaroo!

00:27.094 --> 00:29.261
This is no good.

00:29.330 --> 00:30.728
This chair's old.

00:30.765 --> 00:31.997
Well, so are you.

00:32.066 --> 00:33.665
You don't see me
throwing you away.

00:33.734 --> 00:37.035
Hudaro: [on tv]
you're two years old.

00:37.104 --> 00:39.337
Participant: They said I was
dancing like a chicken,

00:39.373 --> 00:41.006
But I don't remember a thing!

00:41.008 --> 00:43.608
Hudaro is amazing!

00:43.677 --> 00:47.679
Don't miss your chance to see
the unfathomable hudaro!

00:47.748 --> 00:49.881
Can we go?
Can we, please?

00:49.950 --> 00:52.517
He can't be any good
if he's comin' here.

00:52.553 --> 00:56.488
Hudaro: Who dares dare hudaro?
Hudaro dares!

00:56.623 --> 00:59.858
Announcer: Hudaro!
Two nights only, st. John's!

00:59.993 --> 01:01.025
He's playing at school!

01:01.062 --> 01:02.160
No way!

01:02.229 --> 01:03.362
Mike sr: Must be terrible.

01:03.497 --> 01:04.530
Alright, we'll go.

01:04.532 --> 01:05.798
Woo-hoo-hoo-hoo!

01:05.933 --> 01:06.898
Adult mark:<i> Being a newsman,</i>

01:06.934 --> 01:09.501
<i>The old man loved a train wreck.</i>

01:09.537 --> 01:11.937
Mark, I found your math test.

01:11.939 --> 01:13.905
Did you hide this
so I wouldn't find it?

01:14.040 --> 01:16.174
Will I be in less trouble
if I answer honestly?

01:16.210 --> 01:18.910
You are spending too much time
glued to that idiot box!

01:18.946 --> 01:21.079
No show for you until
you get your grades up!

01:21.115 --> 01:22.381
But, mom, it's just a quiz!

01:22.383 --> 01:24.116
The actual test is on Friday.

01:24.118 --> 01:26.117
Come on, mary.
Let the boy...

01:26.153 --> 01:27.586
17.50?!

01:27.655 --> 01:28.853
Good god!

01:28.889 --> 01:30.055
Listen to your mother.
You're not going.

01:30.190 --> 01:31.156
No.

01:31.291 --> 01:33.525
Hudaro: Don't you dare miss it!

01:33.561 --> 01:36.461
["hinterland who's who"
playing on tv]

01:36.464 --> 01:38.063
Good news!

01:38.065 --> 01:41.133
It's not me,
it's not the chair,

01:41.268 --> 01:43.568
It was my pants!

01:43.703 --> 01:46.604
Mary: Oh...
Pop: They were too tight!

01:46.640 --> 01:48.073
Ahh!

01:48.075 --> 01:50.375
Oh, much better!

01:50.411 --> 01:52.010
Turn it up!

01:52.079 --> 01:55.547
♪

01:57.685 --> 01:59.351
What's this about?

01:59.420 --> 02:00.785
Probably
school picture day.

02:00.855 --> 02:02.120
Mom never buys 'em.

02:02.189 --> 02:04.356
I'm not combing
my hair for that.

02:04.491 --> 02:05.958
Adult mark:<i> Fox's folks</i>
<i> had enough kids</i>

02:05.960 --> 02:07.426
<i> To fill their own yearbook,</i>

02:07.428 --> 02:09.494
<i> So they opted for</i>
<i> the watermarked sample.</i>

02:09.497 --> 02:11.029
I like picture day.

02:11.165 --> 02:13.231
You know,
if I'm gonna be an actor,

02:13.267 --> 02:15.033
I'll need an updated headshot.

02:15.035 --> 02:16.902
And I get to trade
photos this year

02:17.037 --> 02:19.238
Now that I finally have friends.

02:19.373 --> 02:21.973
Yeah, fox, you should get one
so we can all trade.

02:22.009 --> 02:23.108
Whatever.

02:23.177 --> 02:24.910
Maybe.

02:24.979 --> 02:26.278
Sister rose: [into mic]
children...

02:26.347 --> 02:29.180
As we enter
the holy season of lent,

02:29.216 --> 02:32.251
We must make sacrifices.

02:32.386 --> 02:35.787
Yes, we encourage you
to give something up for lent.

02:35.789 --> 02:38.523
Perhaps some candy,
or television,

02:38.526 --> 02:41.460
Or video games.

02:41.595 --> 02:45.197
Our lord was beaten
and crucified.

02:45.199 --> 02:47.865
But yes, ms. Fowler,
you could give up...

02:47.902 --> 02:49.468
Candy.

02:49.470 --> 02:51.203
Even-steven.

02:51.205 --> 02:52.270
Ms. Fowler: Yes.

02:52.306 --> 02:54.239
Well, a special guest is here

02:54.374 --> 02:56.808
And he's offered you
a free show.

02:56.810 --> 02:58.343
Adult mark:<i> It couldn't be!</i>

02:58.345 --> 03:01.046
Please welcome,
all the way from las vegas,

03:01.181 --> 03:03.882
The unfathomable hudaro!

03:04.017 --> 03:07.920
[applause & cheering]

03:08.055 --> 03:10.022
[dramatic music playing]

03:10.024 --> 03:12.024
Hello, st. Bridget's!

03:12.026 --> 03:14.893
Who dares dare hudaro?

03:15.028 --> 03:18.530
Hudaro dares!

03:18.532 --> 03:23.701
[applause & cheering]

03:23.737 --> 03:26.038
You!

03:26.040 --> 03:28.673
♪

03:28.742 --> 03:32.778
Seven, six,
hearing only my voice,

03:32.780 --> 03:34.579
Five, four,

03:34.615 --> 03:37.515
And you will become
the world-renowned opera singer,

03:37.585 --> 03:39.451
Madame fowler,

03:39.520 --> 03:42.320
In, three, two, one...

03:42.456 --> 03:43.388
Sing!

03:43.457 --> 03:46.158
[sings sustained note]

03:46.293 --> 03:48.159
[laughter]

03:48.195 --> 03:51.430
[vocalizing]

03:51.432 --> 03:53.965
[applause]

03:53.967 --> 03:55.133
What do you think, children?

03:55.135 --> 03:56.868
Should we leave her like this?

03:56.870 --> 03:59.103
She could tour the world!

03:59.139 --> 04:01.273
[applause continues]

04:01.275 --> 04:03.642
[singing stops]

04:03.777 --> 04:08.613
[applause & cheering]

04:08.616 --> 04:11.717
Thank you, boys and girls!

04:11.719 --> 04:13.351
[quietly]
sorry.

04:13.387 --> 04:17.588
Now, hudaro knows there is magic
in each and every one of you.

04:17.625 --> 04:20.425
So, who would like to
see some more, huh?

04:20.427 --> 04:21.893
Mark: Yes!
Ritche: Yes!

04:21.895 --> 04:23.495
Hudaro can't hear you!

04:23.497 --> 04:26.365
[applause & cheering]

04:28.802 --> 04:31.303
Mom, we have to go!
It was unfathomable!

04:31.305 --> 04:33.638
You better not have
missed math for that!

04:33.641 --> 04:36.975
I don't know, mark.
Tonight?

04:37.110 --> 04:38.576
You haven't heard
the best part yet.

04:38.646 --> 04:39.845
He offered us free tickets!

04:39.980 --> 04:41.646
Free?

04:41.649 --> 04:43.781
Yeah, free for students so long
as they bring a paying adult.

04:43.817 --> 04:48.253
[sighs]
bloody tinker carny.

04:48.388 --> 04:49.588
Pop!

04:49.590 --> 04:50.922
Pants at the dinner table!

04:50.991 --> 04:52.758
I have put on
a bit of weight,

04:52.893 --> 04:54.859
So I'm just gonna
go on the salads.

04:54.928 --> 04:58.196
Don't worry, I'll be
back in pants in no time.

04:58.331 --> 04:59.831
Pancake day!

04:59.966 --> 05:02.000
Oh, for christ's sake.

05:02.002 --> 05:04.336
Adult mark:<i> On the day before</i>
<i>giving something up for lent,</i>

05:04.338 --> 05:05.604
<i> Catholics eat pancakes...</i>

05:05.739 --> 05:07.506
<i> Because religion is weird.</i>

05:07.641 --> 05:10.609
I just started a diet,
and now you're serving dinner

05:10.611 --> 05:13.412
With "cake" in the name.

05:13.547 --> 05:15.180
Temptress!

05:15.182 --> 05:16.214
Pop: Oh, well.

05:16.216 --> 05:17.482
Go on, then.

05:17.518 --> 05:19.083
I'll have three.

05:19.085 --> 05:20.619
Mary: No, you don't.
Pop: What?

05:20.621 --> 05:23.421
Nobody wants you back
in pants more than I do.

05:23.490 --> 05:24.756
[choking sound]

05:24.825 --> 05:27.125
Oh, be careful biting in there!
Don't choke!

05:27.127 --> 05:29.294
Adult mark:<i> The tradition</i> is
<i> that your fortune is hidden</i>

05:29.296 --> 05:30.461
<i> Inside the pancake.</i>

05:30.497 --> 05:32.230
<i> A nail means</i>
<i> you'll be a carpenter,</i>

05:32.232 --> 05:34.800
<i> A button means you'll be</i>
<i> a tailor, a coin means...</i>

05:34.935 --> 05:37.135
Pop: [laughs]
mary: You're gonna be rich!

05:37.204 --> 05:39.604
Does that mean we have
enough money to go to the show?

05:39.640 --> 05:41.072
Enough!

05:41.141 --> 05:43.775
Look, give me a pancake
and I'll buy you a ticket.

05:43.910 --> 05:46.244
That's perfect.

05:46.246 --> 05:47.212
Mom...

05:47.347 --> 05:48.346
The math test is Friday.

05:48.481 --> 05:50.048
I'll do better then, I promise!

05:50.050 --> 05:51.650
Fine!
On one condition!

05:51.785 --> 05:53.384
You get an a.

05:53.420 --> 05:54.786
Mark: D?
Mary: C!

05:54.855 --> 05:56.454
Deal!
Yes, thank you!

05:56.490 --> 05:58.356
Pop: Mmm!
[grunts]

05:58.359 --> 06:00.358
A button!

06:00.361 --> 06:02.794
I told you
pants were in my future!

06:02.830 --> 06:06.831
♪

06:16.677 --> 06:19.277
That's my good makeup.

06:19.346 --> 06:20.745
Picture day is tomorrow,

06:20.748 --> 06:22.614
And I thought you
might buy 'em if I...

06:22.749 --> 06:25.349
Suzanne: Oh, my sacred heart!

06:25.386 --> 06:28.353
[sighs]

06:28.488 --> 06:30.055
Don't you fret, my dear.

06:30.057 --> 06:33.090
We are gonna make you look
just like your poor ol' mudder.

06:34.695 --> 06:35.427
[cosmetics bag unzips]

06:37.898 --> 06:40.031
All right, st john's!

06:40.033 --> 06:42.567
Dick dunphy here
from the mighty...

06:42.603 --> 06:45.637
590 vocm!

06:45.706 --> 06:48.039
[one person claps]

06:48.075 --> 06:51.042
Are you ready for...

06:51.177 --> 06:53.511
Hu-da-row?

06:53.580 --> 06:54.913
[applause & cheering]

06:54.982 --> 06:56.848
Announcer: From vegas
to newfoundland,

06:56.983 --> 07:00.852
The greatest hypnotist on earth!

07:00.854 --> 07:03.721
Woo!

07:03.757 --> 07:06.324
You know this is all a bunch
of gobbledygook, don't ya?

07:06.326 --> 07:08.459
Mom, it's not fake!

07:08.495 --> 07:10.061
It's from las vegas!

07:10.130 --> 07:11.462
Oh, jeez.

07:11.598 --> 07:14.232
Good evening,
ladies and gentlemen!

07:14.367 --> 07:18.736
Tonight, I invite you
to free your subconscious

07:18.772 --> 07:21.873
From the shackles that you
yourself imprisoned it with.

07:22.008 --> 07:24.843
But hudaro is nothing
without volunteers.

07:24.978 --> 07:26.511
So, audience, I ask you...

07:26.513 --> 07:29.681
Who dare dares hudaro?

07:29.816 --> 07:31.750
Woman: Ooh, ooh!
Over here, over here!

07:31.752 --> 07:32.984
Woman: Pick me, pick me!

07:32.986 --> 07:34.553
Hudaro: You, ma'am!
And you!

07:34.688 --> 07:36.421
Woman: Me in the back!
Mary: Mark!

07:36.556 --> 07:38.289
Oh, you little shagger!

07:38.424 --> 07:40.692
And one very
enthusiastic boy, I see.

07:40.827 --> 07:42.227
Adult mark:<i> A stage!</i>

07:42.362 --> 07:44.429
<i> It wasn't hudaro</i>
<i> who had hypnotized me,</i>

07:44.431 --> 07:46.097
<i> It was the audience!</i>

07:46.099 --> 07:48.900
[applause]

07:51.538 --> 07:54.105
Welcome, st. John's!

07:54.107 --> 07:57.441
I am the remarkable mark,

07:57.478 --> 07:59.311
The impossi-boy-list.

07:59.313 --> 08:01.646
I've never been so proud.

08:01.648 --> 08:03.448
I coulda swore
I wore pants.

08:03.583 --> 08:06.317
[applause]

08:06.353 --> 08:07.818
Hudaro: Hear only my voice...

08:07.855 --> 08:09.988
Hearing only my voice...

08:10.057 --> 08:11.623
Only my voice matters...

08:11.758 --> 08:13.458
Adult mark:<i> Concentration</i>
<i> was never my thing.</i>

08:13.593 --> 08:14.793
<i> I was too late.</i>

08:14.928 --> 08:16.795
Two, one,
now listen to the music!

08:16.797 --> 08:18.096
[music starts playing]

08:18.231 --> 08:20.832
Because now you can play
that musical instrument

08:20.834 --> 08:23.702
That you have
always wanted to play.

08:23.704 --> 08:26.070
In fact,
you're the best in the world!

08:26.139 --> 08:27.472
So, play, my orchestra!

08:27.607 --> 08:28.807
Play!

08:28.809 --> 08:30.242
[applause & laughter]

08:30.377 --> 08:31.877
Adult mark:<i> I wasn't</i>
<i> good at studying,</i>

08:32.012 --> 08:33.411
<i> But I was a quick study.</i>

08:33.547 --> 08:34.880
Hudaro: That's it!

08:35.015 --> 08:37.616
What beautiful music!

08:37.751 --> 08:40.985
[laughter & applause]

08:46.426 --> 08:48.059
Hudaro knows
you are faking, boy,

08:48.095 --> 08:50.962
Because a hypnotized subject
never uses props.

08:50.998 --> 08:55.033
Make a fool of me on my stage,
and I will end you.

08:55.035 --> 08:57.902
Beautiful music, no?

08:57.905 --> 09:01.238
[applause & laughter continues]

09:05.512 --> 09:07.045
Adult mark:<i> I might</i>
<i> not have been hypnotized,</i>

09:07.114 --> 09:09.480
<i> But I would have done</i>
<i>anything to stay on that stage.</i>

09:09.550 --> 09:10.882
Ah, so refreshing!

09:10.951 --> 09:12.017
Adult mark:<i> And I did.</i>

09:12.152 --> 09:13.918
You take a sip, mark.

09:13.921 --> 09:16.321
Oh no, mark,
that water is boiling hot!

09:16.390 --> 09:20.925
Mark: Augh, augh!
[audience laughter]

09:20.961 --> 09:26.197
Now it is 140-proof screech!

09:26.233 --> 09:27.732
Adult mark:<i> The more</i>
<i> I faked it,</i>

09:27.734 --> 09:29.200
<i> The more hudaro loved it.</i>

09:29.236 --> 09:31.603
<i> I started to wonder</i>
<i> who was hypnotizing who</i>
